4 Section 3. Section 76-2-304, MCA, is amended to read:
5 "76-2-304. Criteria and guidelines for zoning regulations. (1) Zoning regulations must be:
6 (a) made in accordance with a growth policy; and
7 (b) designed to:
8 (i) secure safety from fire and other dangers;
9 (ii) promote public health, public safety, and the general welfare; and
10 (iii) facilitate the adequate provision of transportation, water, sewerage, schools, parks, and other
11 public requirements.
12 (2) In the adoption of zoning regulations, the municipal governing body shall consider:
13 (a) reasonable provision of adequate light and air;
14 (b) the effect on motorized and nonmotorized transportation systems;
15 (c) promotion of compatible urban growth;
16 (d) the character of the district and its peculiar suitability for particular uses; and
17 (e) conserving the value of buildings and encouraging the most appropriate use of land throughout
18 the jurisdictional area.
19 (3) The use of a residential dwelling for a home-based business as defined in 7-21-4204 is a
20 permitted use, except that this permission does not supersede any of the following:
21 (a) any deed restriction, covenant, or agreement restricting the use of land; and
22 (b) any master deed, bylaw, or other document applicable to a common interest ownership
23 community.
24 (4) A municipality may not require a person as a condition of operating a home-based business to:
25 (a) rezone the property for commercial use; or
26 (b) install or equip fire sprinklers in a detached single-family residence or any residential dwelling
27 with no more than two dwelling units pursuant to 50-60-203.
